		<para>Tracker BI Toolkit is a extensible open desktop. Once installed, the end user can easily add:</para>
		<itemizedlist mark='opencircle'>
			<listitem>
				<para>Tracker Livestock Information Management Features</para>
			</listitem>
			<listitem >
				<para>Tracker iRouter Sensor and Actuator Data Management Features</para>
			</listitem>
			<listitem>
				<para>Generic Eclipse Features from Eclipse or Third Party Repositories.</para>
			</listitem>
		</itemizedlist>
		<para>To install:</para>
		<itemizedlist mark='opencircle'>
			<listitem>
				<para>Down load and extract compressed file to a
			desirable directory.</para>
			</listitem>
			<listitem >
				<para>The top level directory is called tracker.</para>
			</listitem>
			<listitem>
				<para>Invoke the tracker executive inside the top level tracker director.</para>
			</listitem>
		</itemizedlist>
		<para>To Provision the Toolkit with Tools:</para>
		<itemizedlist mark='opencircle'>
			<listitem>
				<para>From the Welcome Screen, which is the first screen presented to the user on a new install, select <emphasis>First Steps</emphasis></para>
			</listitem>
			<listitem >
				<para>From the First Steps Screen, select <emphasis>Learn How to Provision Tracker BI Toolkit</emphasis> and follow the guided cheat sheet.</para>
			</listitem>
		</itemizedlist>
	</section>

